00087 /** 
00088  * \ingroup Sierra
00089  * \defgroup PrivateSierraHelpers Helpers (not available outside this module)
00090  *
00091  * \description
00092  *
00093  *   These routines help parse the Sierra input file.
00094  *
00095  *   The Sierra input file is generally organized as nested blocks
00096  *   bounded by "BEGIN" and "END" strings. The helper parse routines
00097  *   parse specific blocks (e.g. _fc_parseSierra for Sierra blocks,
00098  *   _fc_parseSpotWeld for spot weld blocks, etc.). 
00099  *   Their job is to 
00100  *   1) keep track of 'begin' and 'end's so they know when to exit,
00101  *   2) copy information specific to the block to the FC_SierraInfo struct,
00102  *   3) call appropriate parser functions for encountered blocks.
00103  *
00104  *   If creating a new helper, it is recommended to copy an existing one
00105  *   to get all functions it is supposed to do.
00106  *
00107  *   If one helper needs fixing up or changing for general capabilities,
00108  *   you should fix up ALL helpers.
00109  *
00110  *   Helper functions expect to start with the file handle at a point where 
00111  *   it is pointing at the block's user specified name.
00112  *
00113  *   Helper functions consume one more 'end' than 'begin' (they're caller 
00114  *   saw their 'begin', but they see their own 'end'), so the caller of a
00115  *   helper function needs to decrement it's 'end' count when the
00116  *   helper returns.
00117  *
00118  * \todo The following Fixes apply to all helper parse routines, and perhaps
00119  *   also fc_parseSierraInputFile.
00120  *   - If a read in string doesn't match any known thing, discard the rest 
00121  *     of the line? Could speed things up but probably not necessary.
00122  *   - Routines can't deal with continuation lines (end with "/$" or "/#")
00123  *   - Add a generic read keyword value pair to centralize the code for 
00124  *     dealing with the variations 'keyword = value', 'keyword= value', 
00125  *     'keyword =value', and 'keyword==value' (note the spaces around '='). 
00126  *      BUT there is at least one case when value is more than one word!!! 
00127  *     (function = piecewise linear)
00128  *   - We don't have any early exits, (i.e if an error) & general error 
00129  *     checking
00130  */
00131

00199 /**
00200  * \ingroup  Sierra
00201  * \brief Free memory associated with a FC_SierraInfo struct.
00202  *
00203  * \description
00204  *  
00205  *    This frees allocated members within the struct as well as
00206  *    the struct itself.
00207  *
00208  * \modifications  
00209  *   12/23/04 WSK created. Replaces fc_clearSierraInfo().
00210  */
00211 void fc_freeSierraInfo(
00212   FC_SierraInfo* sierra /**< input - sierra info object */
00213 ) 
00214 {
00215   int i;
00216 
00217   // check input
00218   if (!sierra)
00219     return;
00220 
00221   // log message
00222   fc_printfLogMessage("Freeing sierra info.");
00223 
00224   // release dynamically allocated members (and their members ...)
00225   if (sierra->numFunction > 0) {
00226     for (i = 0; i < sierra->numFunction; i++) {
00227       free(sierra->functions[i]->values);
00228       free(sierra->functions[i]);
00229     }
00230     free(sierra->functions);
00231   }
00232   if (sierra->numSpotWeld > 0) {
00233     for (i = 0; i < sierra->numSpotWeld; i++) 
00234       free(sierra->spotwelds[i]);
00235     free(sierra->spotwelds);
00236   }
00237 
00238   // free this
00239   free(sierra);
00240 }

00242 /**
00243  * \ingroup  Sierra
00244  * \brief Print an FC_SierraInfo struct.
00245  *
00246  * \description
00247  *  
00248  *   Print the contents of an FC_SierraInfo struct.
00249  *

00251  *   2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00252  */
00253 FC_ReturnCode fc_printSierraInfo(
00254   FC_SierraInfo* sierra /**< input - sierra info object */
00255 ) {
00256   int i, j;
00257 
00258   // check input
00259   if (!sierra) {
00260     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
00261     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
00262   }
00263  
00264   printf("Sierra Problem '%s'\n", sierra->name);
00265   fflush(NULL);
00266 
00267   // variables
00268   printf("  Alias for 'displacement' = '%s'\n", sierra->displ_alias);
00269   printf("  Alias for 'force_external' = '%s'\n", sierra->f_ext_alias);
00270   fflush(NULL);
00271 
00272   // functions
00273   printf("  Found %d functions:\n", sierra->numFunction);
00274   for (i = 0; i < sierra->numFunction; i++) {
00275     FC_SierraFuncInfo *function = sierra->functions[i];
00276     printf("    %d: '%s'\n", i, function->name);
00277     printf("      type = '%s'\n", function->type);
00278     printf("      abscissa label = '%s'\n", function->abscissa_label);
00279     printf("      ordinate label = '%s'\n", function->ordinate_label);
00280     printf("      number of values = %d\n", function->numValue);
00281     printf("      values = %f", function->values[0]);
00282     if (function->numValue > 1)
00283       printf("  %f\n",function->values[1]);
00284     else
00285       printf("\n");
00286     if (function->numValue > 2) { 
00287       for (j = 1; j < function->numValue/2; j++)
00288         printf("               %f  %f\n", function->values[j*2], 
00289                function->values[j*2+1]);
00290     }
00291     printf("      min abscissa = %f\n", function->abscissa_min);
00292     printf("      max abscissa = %f\n", function->abscissa_max);
00293     if (function->numValue > 1) {
00294       printf("      min ordinate = %f\n", function->ordinate_min);
00295       printf("      max ordinate = %f\n", function->ordinate_max);
00296     }
00297     else {
00298       printf("      min ordinate = (not applicable)\n");
00299       printf("      max ordinate = (not applicable)\n");
00300     }
00301   }
00302   fflush(NULL);
00303 
00304   // spot welds
00305   printf("  Found %d spot welds:\n", sierra->numSpotWeld);
00306   for (i = 0; i < sierra->numSpotWeld; i++) {
00307     FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo *spotweld = sierra->spotwelds[i];
00308     printf("    %d: '%s'\n", i, spotweld->name);
00309     printf("      node set = '%s' (name = '%s')\n", spotweld->nodeset,
00310            spotweld->nodeset_name);
00311     printf("      surface  = '%s'  (name = '%s')\n", spotweld->surface,
00312            spotweld->surface_name);
00313     printf("      normal displ. function (ID = %d)     = '%s'\n", 
00314            spotweld->normalId, spotweld->normal);
00315     printf("      normal displ. scale factor = %f\n", spotweld->normal_scale);
00316     printf("      tangential displ. function (ID = %d) = '%s'\n", 
00317            spotweld->tangentId, spotweld->tangent);
00318     printf("      tangent displ. scale factor = %f\n", spotweld->tangent_scale);
00319     printf("      failure envelope exponent = %f\n", spotweld->exponent);
00320     printf("      failure decay cycles = %d\n", spotweld->decay_cycles);
00321   }
00322   fflush(NULL);
00323 
00324   return FC_SUCCESS;
00325 }

00327 /**
00328  * \ingroup  Sierra
00329  * \brief Parse a Sierra Input File and put info into FC_SierraInfo struct.
00330  *
00331  * \description
00332  *  
00333  *   Parses a Sierra input file and returns a new FC_SierraInfo object
00334  *   containibg the sierra info. It's memory can be released using
00335  *   fc_freeSierraInfo().
00336  *
00337  *   Currently the parser only returns the information needed to analyze
00338  *   Presto spot welds. However, the parsing routines were written to
00339  *   (hopefully) be easily expanded when additional info is required.
00340  *   See the private documentation for _fc_parseSierra for more
00341  *   details about the parsing process.
00342  *
00343  * \modifications  
00344  *    - 2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00345  *    - 12/23/04 WSK Changed so it creates the FC_SierraInfo object instead
00346  *      of taking it as an object.
00347  */
00348 FC_ReturnCode fc_parseSierraInputFile(
00349   char* filename,         /**< input - the sierra input file */
00350   FC_SierraInfo** sierra  /**< output - sierra info */ 
00351 ) 
00352 {
00353   int i, j;
00354   FC_ReturnCode rc, rc_keep;
00355   int level = 0;
00356   FILE* inputfile;
00357 
00358   // default return
00359   if (sierra)
00360     *sierra = NULL;
00361 
00362   // check input
00363   if (!filename || !sierra) {
00364     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(rc));
00365     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
00366   }
00367 
00368   // open the input file
00369   inputfile = fopen(filename, "r");
00370   if (!inputfile) {
00371         fc_printfErrorMessage("sierra input parser could not open file '%s'\n", 
00372                  filename);
00373     return FC_FILE_IO_ERROR;
00374   }
00375 
00376   // setup sierra
00377   *sierra = malloc(sizeof(FC_SierraInfo));
00378   rc = _fc_initSierraInfo(*sierra);
00379   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
00380     return rc;
00381 
00382   // Loop over lines in the file
00383   while (fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) { 
00384     
00385     // skip comment line 
00386     if (string[0] == '#' || string[0] == '$') 
00387       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00388     
00389     // end block 
00390     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
00391       level--;
00392       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00393     }
00394     
00395     // begin block 0
00396     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "begin")) {
00397       level++;
00398 
00399       // determine type of begin
00400       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00401       
00402       // sierra block
00403       if (!strcasecmp(string, "sierra")) {
00404         rc = _fc_parseSierra(inputfile, *sierra);
00405         if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
00406           return rc;
00407         level--;
00408       }
00409     }
00410   }
00411   
00412   // close the input file
00413   fclose(inputfile);
00414 
00415   if (level != 0) 
00416     fc_printfWarningMessage("parser: begins & ends do not match.");
00417 
00418   // Make extra info for spot welds
00419   rc_keep = FC_SUCCESS; // keep track of any errors
00420   for (i = 0; i < (*sierra)->numSpotWeld; i++) {
00421     FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo* spotweld = (*sierra)->spotwelds[i];
00422 
00423     // make connections to the functions
00424     spotweld->normalId = -1;
00425     spotweld->tangentId = -1;
00426     spotweld->normal_p = NULL;
00427     spotweld->tangent_p = NULL;
00428     for (j = 0; j < (*sierra)->numFunction; j++) {
00429       FC_SierraFuncInfo* function = (*sierra)->functions[j];
00430       if (!strcasecmp(spotweld->normal, function->name)) {
00431         spotweld->normalId = j;
00432         spotweld->normal_p = function;
00433       }
00434       if (!strcasecmp(spotweld->tangent, function->name)) {
00435         spotweld->tangentId = j;
00436         spotweld->tangent_p = function;
00437       }
00438     }
00439     if (spotweld->normalId == -1 || spotweld->tangentId == -1) {      
00440       rc_keep = FC_ERROR; // don't return, try to set up other spotwelds
00441       fc_printfWarningMessage("function for spotweld '%s' not found\n", 
00442               spotweld->name);
00443     }
00444 
00445     // make names used in database (e.g. 'nodelist_12' -> 'Node set ID 12'
00446     // and 'surface_3002' -> 'Side set ID 3003')
00447     sprintf(spotweld->nodeset_name, "nodelist_%s", &(spotweld->nodeset[9]));
00448     sprintf(spotweld->surface_name, "surface_hex8_quadface4_%s", &(spotweld->surface[8]));
00449   }
00450   
00451   return rc_keep;
00452 }

00454 /**
00455  * \ingroup  PrivateSierraHelpers
00456  * \brief Parse a Sierra block.
00457  *
00458  * \description
00459  *
00460  *   This routines parses a Sierra block. It calls helper parsers
00461  *   for function definition blocks and the presto procedure block.
00462  *
00463  *   What follows is applicable to all helper parse routines.
00464  * 
00465  *   The Sierra input file is generally organized as nested blocks
00466  *   bounded by "BEGIN" and "END" strings. The helper parse routines
00467  *   parse specific blocks (e.g. _fc_parseSierra for Sierra blocks,
00468  *   _fc_parseSpotWeld for spot weld blocks, etc.). 
00469  *   Their job is to 
00470  *   1) keep track of 'begin' and 'end's so they know when to exit,
00471  *   2) copy information specific to the block to the FC_SierraInfo struct,
00472  *   3) call appropriate parser functions for encountered blocks.
00473  *
00474  *   If creating a new helper, it is recommended to copy an existing one
00475  *   to get all functions it is supposed to do.
00476  *
00477  *   If one helper needs fixing up or changing for general capabilities,
00478  *   you should fix up ALL helpers.
00479  *
00480  *   Helper functions expect to start with the file handle at a point where 
00481  *   it is pointing at the block's user specified name.
00482  *
00483  *   Helper functions consume one more 'end' than 'begin' (they're caller 
00484  *   saw their 'begin', but they see their own 'end'), so the caller of a
00485  *   helper function needs to decrement it's 'end' count when the
00486  *   helper returns.
00487  *
00488  * \modifications  
00489  *   2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00490  */
00491 FC_ReturnCode _fc_parseSierra(FILE* inputfile, FC_SierraInfo* sierra) {
00492   FC_ReturnCode rc; // return code
00493   int level = 1;
00494   int parent_level = level - 1;
00495 
00496   // get block name
00497   fscanf(inputfile, "%s", sierra->name);
00498 
00499   // loop over lines until matching end found
00500   while (level > parent_level  &&  fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00501     
00502     // skip comment line 
00503     if (string [0] == '#' || string[0] == '$')
00504       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00505     
00506     // end block
00507     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
00508       level--;
00509       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00510     }
00511 
00512     // begin block 
00513     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "begin")) {
00514       level++;
00515 
00516       // get type of begin
00517       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00518       
00519       // definition block 1
00520       if (!strcasecmp(string, "definition")) {
00521         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00522         if (!strcasecmp(string, "for")) {
00523           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00524           if (!strcasecmp(string, "function")) {
00525             rc = _fc_parseDefinitionForFunction(inputfile, sierra);
00526             if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
00527               return rc;
00528             level--;
00529           }
00530         }
00531       } // definition block 1
00532             
00533       // procedure block
00534       else if (!strcasecmp(string, "presto")) {
00535         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00536         if (!strcasecmp(string, "procedure")) {
00537           rc = _fc_parsePrestoProcedure(inputfile, sierra);
00538           if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
00539             return rc;
00540           level--;
00541         }
00542       } // procedure block
00543     } // begin block
00544   } // while loop
00545 
00546   return FC_SUCCESS;
00547 }
00548 
00549 /**
00550  * \ingroup  PrivateSierraHelpers
00551  * \brief Parse a function definition block
00552  *
00553  * \description
00554  *
00555  *   This routines parses a function definition block. It creates
00556  *   a FC_SierraFuncInfo struct and adds it to the FC_SierraInfo struct's
00557  *   array of functions. It reads in the sierra info and also calculates the
00558  *   min and max values of the ordinate and abscissa. It does not call any
00559  *   other helper parse routines.
00560  *
00561  *   See _fc_parseSierra for generic information about all helper parse 
00562  *   routines.
00563  *
00564  * \modifications  
00565  *   2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00566  *
00567  *   2003-AUG-20  W Koegler  Fixed bug with comments within values block
00568  */
00569 FC_ReturnCode _fc_parseDefinitionForFunction(FILE* inputfile, FC_SierraInfo* sierra) {
00570   int level = 1;
00571   int parent_level = level - 1;
00572   int numFunction;
00573   FC_SierraFuncInfo* function;
00574   void* temp;
00575   
00576   // make room for new function
00577   numFunction = sierra->numFunction;
00578   temp = realloc(sierra->functions, sizeof(FC_SierraFuncInfo*)*(numFunction + 1));
00579   if (temp == NULL) {
00580     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00581     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00582   }
00583   sierra->functions = temp;
00584   sierra->functions[numFunction] = malloc(sizeof(FC_SierraFuncInfo));
00585   if (sierra->functions[numFunction] == NULL) {
00586     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00587     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00588   }
00589   sierra->numFunction++;
00590 
00591   // initialize function
00592   function = sierra->functions[sierra->numFunction-1];
00593   strcpy(function->abscissa_label, "");
00594   strcpy(function->ordinate_label, "");
00595   function->numValue = 0;
00596   function->values = NULL;
00597 
00598   // get block name
00599   fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->name);
00600   
00601   // loop over lines until matching end found
00602   while (level > parent_level  && fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00603 
00604     // skip comment line
00605     if (string[0] == '#' || string[0] == '$')
00606       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00607 
00608     // end
00609     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
00610       level--;
00611       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00612     }
00613 
00614     // type
00615     else if (!strncasecmp(string, "type", 4)) {
00616       int len = strlen(string);
00617       if (len == 4) {
00618         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00619         if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=type'
00620           strcpy(function->type, &string[1]);
00621         else
00622           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->type);
00623       }
00624       else if (len == 5) // probably was 'type='
00625         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->type);
00626       else if (len > 5) // probably was 'type=type'
00627         strcpy(function->type, &string[5]);
00628       if (!strcasecmp(function->type, "piecewise")) {
00629         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00630         sprintf(&function->type[strlen(function->type)], " %s", string);
00631       }
00632     } // end type
00633 
00634     // abscissa label
00635     else if (!strncasecmp(string, "abscissa", 8)) {
00636       int len = strlen(string);
00637       if (len == 8) {
00638         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00639         if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
00640           strcpy(function->abscissa_label, &string[1]);
00641         else
00642           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->abscissa_label);
00643       }
00644       else if (len == 9) // probably was 'abscissa='
00645         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->abscissa_label);
00646       else if (len > 9) // probably was 'abscissa=name'
00647         strcpy(function->abscissa_label, &string[9]);
00648     }  // end abscissa label
00649 
00650     // ordinate label
00651     else if (!strncasecmp(string, "ordinate", 8)) {
00652       int len = strlen(string);
00653       if (len == 8) {
00654         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00655         if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
00656           strcpy(function->ordinate_label, &string[1]);
00657         else
00658           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->ordinate_label);
00659       }
00660       else if (len == 9) // probably was 'ordinate='
00661         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", function->ordinate_label);
00662       else if (len > 9) // probably was 'ordinate=name'
00663         strcpy(function->ordinate_label, &string[9]);
00664     }  // end ordinate label
00665 
00666     // begin block
00667     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "begin")) {
00668       level++;
00669 
00670       // get type of begin
00671       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00672     
00673       // values block
00674       if (!strcasecmp(string, "values")) {
00675         while (fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00676 
00677           // skip comment line
00678           if (string[0] == '#' || string[0] == '$')
00679             fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00680 
00681           // end;
00682           else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
00683             level--;
00684             break;
00685           }
00686 
00687           // read the values and save the max
00688           else {
00689             double flt = atof(string);
00690             temp = realloc(function->values, 
00691                                  sizeof(double)*(function->numValue + 1));
00692             if (temp == NULL) {
00693               fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00694               return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00695             }
00696             function->values = temp;
00697             function->values[function->numValue] = flt;
00698             function->numValue++;
00699 
00700             if (function->numValue%2 == 1) { // odd = abscissa (x)
00701               if (function->numValue == 1) {
00702                 function->abscissa_min = flt;
00703                 function->abscissa_max = flt;
00704               }
00705               else {
00706                 if (flt < function->abscissa_min)
00707                   function->abscissa_min = flt;
00708                 else if (flt > function->abscissa_max)
00709                   function->abscissa_max = flt;
00710               }
00711             }
00712             else {// even's
00713               if (function->numValue == 2) {
00714                 function->ordinate_min = flt;
00715                 function->ordinate_max = flt;
00716               }
00717               else {
00718                 if (flt < function->ordinate_min)
00719                   function->ordinate_min = flt;
00720                 else if (flt > function->ordinate_max)
00721                   function->ordinate_max = flt;
00722               } 
00723             }
00724           }
00725         }
00726       } // values block
00727     } // begin block
00728   } // while loop
00729 
00730   return FC_SUCCESS;
00731 }

00752 
00753   // get block name
00754   fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string); // discard
00755 
00756   // loop over lines until matching end found
00757   while (level > parent_level  &&  fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00758

00765       level--;
00766       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);

00862 /**
00863  * \ingroup  PrivateSierraHelpers
00864  * \brief Parse a results output block
00865  *
00866  * \description
00867  *
00868  *   This routines parses a results output block. It saves the
00869  *   aliases for the variables "displacements" and "force_external". 
00870  *   It does not call any other helper parse routines.
00871  *
00872  *   See _fc_parseSierra for generic information about all helper parse 
00873  *   routines.
00874  *
00875  * \modifications  
00876  *   2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00877  */
00878 FC_ReturnCode _fc_parseResultsOutput(FILE* inputfile, FC_SierraInfo* sierra) {
00879   int level = 1;
00880   int parent_level = level - 1;
00881 
00882   // get block name
00883   fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00884   
00885   // loop over lines until matching end found
00886   while (level > parent_level  && fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00887 
00888     startOfWhile: 
00889 
00890     // skip comment line
00891     if (string[0] == '#' || string[0] == '$')
00892       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00893 
00894     // end
00895     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
00896       level--;
00897       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00898     }
00899 
00900     // begin block
00901     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "begin")) {
00902       level++;
00903     }
00904 
00905     // FIX instead of grabbing specific vars, collect all (& node/elem etc)
00906     // grab the alias for displacement & force_external
00907     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "nodal") || !strcasecmp(string, "element") 
00908              || !strcasecmp(string, "global")) {
00909       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00910       if (!strncasecmp(string, "variables", 9)) {
00911         // get the variable name
00912         int len = strlen(string);
00913         if (len == 9) {
00914           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00915           if (string[0] == '='  &&  strlen(string) > 1) // '=variable_name'
00916             strcpy(string, &string[1]);
00917           else
00918             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00919         }
00920         else if (len == 10) // we probably scanned in 'variables='
00921           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
00922         else if (len > 10)  // we probably scanned in 'variables=variable_name'
00923           strcpy(string, &string[10]);
00924 
00925         // if the next string is not 'as' we've read in the next line!
00926         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", temp_string);
00927         if (strcasecmp(temp_string, "as") && level > parent_level) {
00928           strcpy(string, temp_string);
00929           goto startOfWhile;  // start another loop without a new scanf
00930         }
00931 
00932         // get the alias name
00933         if (!strcasecmp(string, "force_external"))
00934           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", sierra->f_ext_alias);
00935         else if (!strcasecmp(string, "displacement"))
00936           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", sierra->displ_alias);
00937       }
00938     } // force external
00939   } // while loop
00940 
00941   return FC_SUCCESS;
00942 }

00944 /**
00945  * \ingroup  PrivateSierraHelpers
00946  * \brief Parse a spot weld block
00947  *
00948  * \description
00949  *
00950  *   This routines parses a spot weld block. It creates a FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo
00951  *   struct and adds it to the FC_SierraInfo struct's array of spot welds.
00952  *   It reads int the sierra info (the sierra parser will create the
00953  *   function indices after all spot welds and functions have been parsed).
00954  *   It does not call any other helper parse routines.
00955  *
00956  *   See _fc_parseSierra for generic information about all helper parse 
00957  *   routines.
00958  *
00959  * \modifications  
00960  *   2003-JUN-24  W Koegler  Created.
00961  */
00962 FC_ReturnCode _fc_parseSpotWeld(FILE* inputfile, FC_SierraInfo* sierra) {
00963   int level = 1;
00964   int parent_level = level - 1;
00965   int numSpotWeld;
00966   FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo* spotweld;
00967   void *temp;
00968 
00969   // make room for new spotweld
00970   numSpotWeld = sierra->numSpotWeld;
00971   temp = realloc(sierra->spotwelds, 
00972                  sizeof(FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo*)*(numSpotWeld + 1));
00973   if (temp == NULL)
00974     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00975   sierra->spotwelds = temp;
00976   sierra->spotwelds[numSpotWeld] = malloc(sizeof(FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo));
00977   if (sierra->spotwelds[numSpotWeld] == NULL) {
00978     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00979     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00980   }
00981   sierra->numSpotWeld++;
00982 
00983   // initialize new spotweld
00984   spotweld = sierra->spotwelds[sierra->numSpotWeld-1];
00985   spotweld->normal_scale = 1.0F;
00986   spotweld->tangent_scale = 1.0F;
00987   spotweld->nodeset_name[0] = '\0';
00988   spotweld->surface_name[0] = '\0';
00989 
00990   // get block name
00991   fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->name);
00992   
00993   // loop over lines until matching end found
00994   while (level > parent_level  && fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string) > 0) {
00995 
00996     // skip comment line
00997     if (string[0] == '#' || string[0] == '$')
00998       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
00999 
01000     // end
01001     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "end")) {
01002       level--;
01003       fscanf(inputfile, "%[^\n]%1[\n]", string, temp_string);
01004     }
01005 
01006     // begin block
01007     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "begin")) {
01008       level++;
01009     }
01010 
01011     // node set name
01012     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "node")) {
01013       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01014       if (!strncasecmp(string, "set", 3)) {
01015         int len = strlen(string);
01016         if (len == 3) {
01017           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01018           if (string[0] == '='  &&  strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
01019             strcpy(spotweld->nodeset, &string[1]);
01020           else
01021             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->nodeset);
01022         }
01023         else if (len == 4) // probably was 'set='
01024           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->nodeset);
01025         else if (len > 4) // probably was 'set=name' 
01026           strcpy(spotweld->nodeset, &string[4]);
01027       }
01028     }
01029 
01030     // surface name
01031     else if (!strncasecmp(string, "surface", 7)) {
01032       int len = strlen(string);
01033       if (len == 7) {
01034         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01035         if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
01036           strcpy(spotweld->surface, &string[1]);
01037         else
01038           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->surface);
01039       }
01040       else if (len == 8) // probably was 'surface='
01041         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->surface);
01042       else if (len > 8) // probably was 'surface=name'
01043         strcpy(spotweld->surface, &string[8]);
01044     }
01045 
01046     // normal displacement function name or scale factor
01047     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "normal")) {
01048       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01049       if (!strcasecmp(string, "displacement")) {
01050         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01051 
01052         // function name
01053         if (!strncasecmp(string, "function", 8)) {
01054           int len = strlen(string);
01055           if (len == 8) {
01056             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01057             if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
01058               strcpy(spotweld->normal, &string[1]);
01059             else
01060               fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->normal);
01061           }
01062           else if (len == 9) // probably was 'function='
01063             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->normal);
01064           else if (len > 9) // probably was 'function=name'
01065             strcpy(spotweld->normal, &string[9]);
01066         } // end function name
01067 
01068         // scale factor
01069         else if (!strcasecmp(string, "scale")) {
01070           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01071           if (!strncasecmp(string, "factor", 6)) {
01072             int len = strlen(string);
01073             if (len == 6) {
01074               fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01075               if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=num'
01076                 spotweld->normal_scale = atof(&string[1]);
01077               else
01078                 fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->normal_scale);
01079             }
01080             else if (len == 7) // probably was 'scale='
01081               fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->normal_scale);
01082             else if (len > 7) // probably was 'scale=num'
01083               spotweld->normal_scale = atof(&string[7]);
01084           } 
01085         } // end scale factor
01086       }
01087     } // normal displacement function name or scale factor
01088 
01089     // tangential displacement function name or scale factor
01090     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "tangential")) {
01091       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01092       if (!strcasecmp(string, "displacement")) {
01093         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01094 
01095         // function name
01096         if (!strncasecmp(string, "function", 8)) {
01097           int len = strlen(string);
01098           if (len == 8) {
01099             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01100             if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=name'
01101               strcpy(spotweld->tangent, &string[1]);
01102             else
01103               fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->tangent);
01104           }
01105           else if (len == 9) // probably was 'function='
01106             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", spotweld->tangent);
01107           else if (len > 9) // probably was 'function=name'
01108             strcpy(spotweld->tangent, &string[9]);
01109         } // end function name
01110 
01111         // scale factor
01112         else if (!strcasecmp(string, "scale")) {
01113           fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01114           if (!strncasecmp(string, "factor", 6)) {
01115             int len = strlen(string);
01116             if (len == 6) {
01117               fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01118               if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=num'
01119                 spotweld->tangent_scale = atof(&string[1]);
01120               else
01121                 fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->tangent_scale);
01122             }
01123             else if (len == 7) // probably was 'scale='
01124               fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->tangent_scale);
01125             else if (len > 7) // probably was 'scale=num'
01126               spotweld->tangent_scale = atof(&string[7]);
01127           } 
01128         } // end scale factor
01129       }
01130     } // tangential displacement function name or scale factor
01131 
01132     // failure envelope exponent & decay cycles
01133     else if (!strcasecmp(string, "failure")) {
01134       fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01135 
01136       // envelope exponent
01137       if (!strcasecmp(string, "envelope")) {
01138         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01139         if (!strncasecmp(string, "exponent", 8)) {
01140           int len = strlen(string);
01141           if (len == 8) {
01142             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01143             if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=number'
01144               spotweld->exponent = atof(&string[1]);
01145             else
01146               fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->exponent);
01147           }
01148           else if (len == 9) // probably was 'function='
01149             fscanf(inputfile, "%lf", &spotweld->exponent);
01150           else if (len > 9) // probably was 'function=name'
01151             spotweld->exponent = atof(&string[9]);
01152         }
01153       } // end envelope exponent
01154 
01155       // decay cycles
01156       if (!strcasecmp(string, "decay")) {
01157         fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01158         if (!strncasecmp(string, "cycles", 6)) {
01159           int len = strlen(string);
01160           if (len == 6) {
01161             fscanf(inputfile, "%s", string);
01162             if (string[0] == '=' && strlen(string) > 1) // probably '=number'
01163               spotweld->decay_cycles = atoi(&string[1]);
01164             else
01165               fscanf(inputfile, "%d", &spotweld->decay_cycles);
01166           }
01167           else if (len == 7) // probably was 'cycles='
01168             fscanf(inputfile, "%d", &spotweld->decay_cycles);
01169           else if (len > 7) // probably was 'cycles=num'
01170             spotweld->decay_cycles = atoi(&string[7]);
01171         }
01172       } // end envelope exponent
01173       
01174     } // failure envelope exponent
01175 
01176   } // while loop
01177 
01178   return FC_SUCCESS;
01179 }

01181 /**
01182  * \ingroup  Sierra
01183  * \brief Compute the failure parameter for a spot weld.
01184  *
01185  * \description
01186  *
01187  *    The failure parameter is calculated based on the distance between the
01188  *    node of the node set and the point of attachment on the sideset of the
01189  *    spotweld. The attachment remains intact as long as ufail remains less
01190  *    than zero
01191  *
01192  *    ufail = (unorm/umaxnorm)^p + (utang/umaxtang)^p 
01193  *
01194  *    where unorm and utang are the normal and tangential components of the
01195  *    distance between the node and side sets, and umaxnorm and umaxtang are
01196  *    the maximum displacements in the functions defining the spotweld. The
01197  *    caller is responsible for freeing the created params array.
01198  *
01199  *    The index of the time step at which the spot weld is considered to have
01200  *    failed is also returned. (A value of -1 indicates that the spot weld did
01201  *    not fail.) This is when ufail >= 1.
01202  *
01203  * \modifications 
01204  *    - 2003-SEP-08  W Koegler  Changed so that it also does the broken
01205  *      characterization.
01206  *    - 06/22/2004 WSK Changed to take subsets instead of meshes for
01207  *      the node and side sets.
01208  */
01209 FC_ReturnCode fc_evalPrestoSpotWeld(
01210   FC_SierraSpotWeldInfo* spotweld, /**< input - Sierra spot weld info */
01211   FC_Subset node_set,  /**< input - node set specifying the spot weld */
01212   FC_Subset side_set,  /**< input - side set specifying the surface */
01213   int numStep,             /**< input - the number of time steps */
01214   FC_Variable* node_displs, /**< input - array of coord displacements on the
01215                                      node set */ 
01216   FC_Variable* side_displs, /**< input - array of coord displacements on the 
01217                                            side set */
01218   double** ufails_p, /**< output - created array of failure parameters per step */
01219   int *broken_id     /**< output - the step at which the spot weld fails 
01220                                 (-1 = no failure */
01221 ) {
01222   FC_ReturnCode rc;
01223   int i, j, k;
01224   int numMember, nodesetID, sidesetID, *temp_int_array, dim, temp_num;
01225   int side_numVert, *side_vertexIDs;
01226   FC_AssociationType assoc;
01227   FC_ElementType elemtype;
01228   FC_Mesh node_mesh, side_mesh, temp_mesh;
01229   double umaxnorm, umaxtang, exponent;
01230   double unorm, utang; 
01231   double* ufails;
01232   int numParam;
01233   double* params;
01234   
01235   // default return values
01236   if (ufails_p)
01237     *ufails_p = NULL;
01238   if (broken_id)
01239     *broken_id = -1;
01240   
01241   // check input
01242   if (!spotweld || numStep < 1 || !node_displs || !side_displs || 
01243       !ufails_p || !broken_id) {
01244     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
01245     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
01246   }
01247   
01248   // get parent meshes for subsets and make sure have same dim
01249   fc_getMeshFromSubset(node_set, &node_mesh);
01250   fc_getMeshFromSubset(side_set, &side_mesh);
01251   fc_getMeshDim(node_mesh, &dim);
01252   fc_getMeshDim(side_mesh, &temp_num);
01253   if (dim != temp_num) {
01254     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
01255     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
01256   }
01257   
01258   // make sure node displs are on the same mesh as node set
01259   for (i = 0; i < numStep; i++) {
01260     fc_getMeshFromVariable(node_displs[i], &temp_mesh);
01261     if (!FC_HANDLE_EQUIV(temp_mesh, node_mesh)) {
01262       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
01263       return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
01264     }
01265   }
01266   
01267   // make sure side displaces are on the same mesh as side set
01268   for (i = 0; i < numStep; i++) {
01269     fc_getMeshFromVariable(side_displs[i], &temp_mesh);
01270     if (!FC_HANDLE_EQUIV(temp_mesh, side_mesh)) {
01271       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
01272       return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
01273     }
01274   }
01275   
01276   // Get member ID of node set and make sure is o.k. node set
01277   rc = fc_getSubsetMembersAsArray(node_set, &numMember, &temp_int_array);
01278   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01279     return rc;
01280   if (numMember != 1)
01281     return FC_ERROR;
01282   nodesetID = temp_int_array[0];
01283   free(temp_int_array);
01284   rc = fc_getSubsetInfo(node_set, NULL, NULL, &assoc);
01285   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01286     return rc;
01287   if (assoc != FC_AT_VERTEX)
01288     return FC_ERROR;
01289   
01290   // Get member ID and vertexIDs of side set
01291   rc = fc_getSubsetMembersAsArray(side_set, &numMember, &temp_int_array);
01292   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01293     return rc;
01294   if (numMember != 1)
01295     return FC_ERROR;
01296   sidesetID = temp_int_array[0];
01297   free(temp_int_array);
01298   rc = fc_getSubsetInfo(side_set, NULL, NULL, &assoc);
01299   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01300     return rc;
01301   if (assoc == FC_AT_ELEMENT) {
01302     int* conns;
01303     rc = fc_getMeshElementConnsPtr(side_mesh, &conns);
01304     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01305       return rc;
01306     fc_getMeshElementType(side_mesh, &elemtype);
01307     side_numVert = fc_getElementTypeNumVertex(elemtype);
01308     side_vertexIDs = &conns[sidesetID*side_numVert]; // don't free
01309   }
01310   else if (assoc == FC_AT_FACE) {
01311     FC_ElementType* side_faceTypes;
01312     int maxNumVertPerFace, *numVertPerFace, *faceConns;
01313     rc = fc_getMeshFaceTypesPtr(side_mesh, &side_faceTypes);
01314     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01315       return rc;
01316     rc = fc_getMeshFaceConnsPtr(side_mesh, &numVertPerFace, &maxNumVertPerFace,
01317                                 &faceConns);
01318     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01319       return rc;
01320     elemtype = side_faceTypes[sidesetID];
01321     side_numVert = numVertPerFace[sidesetID];
01322     side_vertexIDs = &faceConns[sidesetID*maxNumVertPerFace]; // don't free
01323   }
01324   else {
01325     fc_printfErrorMessage("Sorry, fc_evalPrestoSpotWeld does not "
01326                           "handle sidesets with association %s yet\n",
01327                           fc_getAssociationTypeText(assoc));
01328     return FC_ERROR;
01329   }
01330   // FIX take this out when this routine can do other things
01331   if (elemtype != FC_ET_QUAD) {
01332     fc_printfErrorMessage("Sorry, fc_evalPrestoSpotWeld only does "
01333                           "quad sidesets at the moment\n");
01334     return FC_ERROR;
01335   }
01336   
01337   // get critical displs from spot weld info
01338   umaxnorm = spotweld->normal_p->abscissa_max;
01339   umaxtang = spotweld->tangent_p->abscissa_max;
01340   exponent = spotweld->exponent;
01341   
01342   // determine the params to locate attachment site in side set
01343   // FIX: make this work for a tri too!
01344   {
01345     FC_Coords side_vertCoords[4]; // array of side vertex coords, max 4 for quads
01346     FC_Coords attach_orig; // coordinates of attachment on side set at t0
01347     double* node_mesh_coords;
01348     double* side_mesh_coords;
01349    
01350     rc = fc_getMeshCoordsPtr(node_mesh, &node_mesh_coords);
01351     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01352       return rc;
01353     rc = fc_getMeshCoordsPtr(side_mesh, &side_mesh_coords);
01354     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01355       return rc;
01356     
01357     for (i = 0; i < side_numVert; i++) {
01358       for (j = 0; j < dim; j++)
01359         side_vertCoords[i][j] = side_mesh_coords[side_vertexIDs[i]*dim+j];
01360       for (j = dim; j < 3; j++)
01361         side_vertCoords[i][j] = 0.;
01362     }
01363     
01364     // FC_Coords always have 3 dimensions, pad with zeros
01365     for (i = 0; i < dim; i++) 
01366       attach_orig[i] = node_mesh_coords[nodesetID*dim+i];
01367     for (i = dim; i < 3; i++)
01368       attach_orig[i] = 0.;
01369     
01370     _fc_calcQuadParams(side_vertCoords, attach_orig, &numParam, &params);
01371     if (numParam != 2 )
01372       return FC_ERROR;
01373     // FIX? remove when we think things are working, or add reasonable err?
01374     if (params[0] < 0. || params[0] > 1. || params[1] < 0. || params[1] > 1.) {
01375       free(params);
01376       return FC_ERROR;
01377     }
01378   }
01379   
01380   // create room for return values
01381   ufails = malloc(sizeof(double)*numStep);
01382   if (ufails == NULL) {
01383     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01384     free(params);
01385     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01386   }
01387   for (i = 0; i < numStep; i++)
01388     ufails[i] = -1.;
01389   
01390   // For each step
01391   for (i = 0; i < numStep; i++) {
01392     int vertexID;
01393     double* node_displ_coords;  // displaced vertex coords for node mesh
01394     double* side_displ_coords;  // displaced vertex coords for side mesh
01395     FC_Coords side_vertCoords[4]; // array of coords for side vertices (max 4)
01396     FC_Coords node_point, side_point;
01397     double dist[3], norm[3];
01398     
01399     // get node coordinates
01400     rc = fc_getDisplacedMeshCoords(node_mesh, node_displs[i], 
01401                                    &node_displ_coords);
01402     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
01403       free(params);
01404       free(ufails);
01405       return rc;
01406     }
01407     for (j = 0; j < 3; j++)
01408       node_point[j] = node_displ_coords[dim*nodesetID+j];
01409     free(node_displ_coords);
01410     
01411     // get attachment on side set coordinates & normal of sideset
01412     rc = fc_getDisplacedMeshCoords(side_mesh, side_displs[i], 
01413                                    &side_displ_coords);
01414     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
01415       free(params);
01416       free(ufails);
01417       return rc;
01418     }
01419     for (j = 0; j < side_numVert; j++) {
01420       vertexID = side_vertexIDs[j];
01421       for (k = 0; k < dim; k++) 
01422         side_vertCoords[j][k] = side_displ_coords[vertexID*dim + k];
01423       for (k = dim; k < 3; k++)
01424         side_vertCoords[j][k] = 0.;
01425     }
01426     _fc_calcQuadLocation(side_vertCoords, numParam, params, &side_point);
01427     _fc_calcSurfaceNormal(side_numVert, side_vertCoords, &norm);
01428     free(side_displ_coords);
01429     
01430     // create a vector from side point to node point
01431     for (j = 0; j < 3; j++)
01432       dist[j] = node_point[j] - side_point[j];
01433     
01434     // decompose distance vector along sideset's normal
01435     _fc_decomposeVector(3, dist, dim, norm, &unorm, &utang);
01436     
01437     // calculate ufail
01438     // fabs needed - unorm and untang might be negative and exponent odd
01439     ufails[i] = pow(fabs(unorm/umaxnorm), exponent) + 
01440       pow(fabs(utang/umaxtang), exponent);
01441   }
01442   free(params);
01443   
01444   // assign return values
01445   *ufails_p = ufails;
01446   
01447   // decide if and when the spot weld breaks 
01448   // (this is when ufail first goes above 1)
01449   for (i = 0; i < numStep; i++) {
01450     if (ufails[i] > 1.0 || FC_VALUE_EQUIV(ufails[i], 1.0, 10*DBL_EPSILON,
01451                            DBL_MIN)) {
01452       *broken_id = i; 
01453       break;
01454     }
01455   }
01456   
01457   return FC_SUCCESS;
01458 }
